name: Microbiology Chapter 25 Homework
description: Homework questions for Chapter 25, focusing on the circulatory system.
subject: Microbiology

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The pulmonary circuit carries oxygenated blood into the lungs.
questions.explanation: The pulmonary circuit carries deoxygenated blood from the right ventricle to the lungs and returns oxygenated blood from the lungs to the left atrium.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The heart is a muscle that acts as a pump.
questions.explanation: The heart is a muscular organ composed of cardiac muscle that contracts to pump blood throughout the body.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The human heart consists of 3 chambers.
questions.explanation: The human heart has four chambers: two upper chambers (the atria) and two lower chambers (the ventricles).

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The cardiac output of females is right around 4.9L.
questions.explanation: On average, the cardiac output for a resting female is approximately 4.9 L/min.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: Capillaries are very thin, only about 1 cell layer in diameter.
questions.explanation: Capillaries have very thin walls, typically only one endothelial cell thick, to allow for the efficient exchange of substances between the blood and surrounding tissues.
